Use geom_histogram to create a histogram showing the number of unemployed by age.

Then facet the graph based on biological sex. Hint: geom_histogram is almost the same as geom_bar, but is better suited to plotting continuous data because of the binning.

benefits %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age, fill = sex)
         )+
  geom_histogram(col = "white")+
  facet_wrap(~ sex)+
  labs(x = "Age",
       y = "Count",
       fill = "Gender",
       title = "Unemployed")

benefits %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age, fill = sex)
         )+
  geom_histogram(col = "white")+
  facet_grid(married ~ sex,
             labeller = "label_both")

ggplot(benefits) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(x = age, fill = sex), col = "white") + 
  facet_wrap(~ sex, ncol = 2, scales = "free_y")
